6000|$|Now, {{while they}} spake, <b>I</b> <b>saw</b> <b>my</b> <b>father's</b> face [...] Grow long and troubled like a rising moon, [...] Inflamed with wrath: he started on his feet, [...] Tore the king's letter, snowed it down, and rent [...] The {{wonder of the}} loom through warp and woof [...] From skirt to skirt; and at the last he sware [...] That he would send a hundred {{thousand}} men, [...] And bring her in a whirlwind: then he chewed [...] The thrice-turned cud of wrath, and cooked his spleen, [...] Communing with his captains of the war.|$|R
